---
By: Diogenes
Locus:
  Page: 433
  Verse: 8
Tags:
  - Simplicity
---
Simplicity You lose the very life you seek when you wallow in stupid
luxuries. You don’t need nine-tenths of the things you scramble for. Don’t
be afraid to have nothing. Happiness is not what you have, but who you are.
You are already who you need to be.
